1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:03,090
We can divide categorical data types further into

2

00:00:03,090  -->  00:00:06,125
categorical ordinal and categorical nominal.

3

00:00:06,125  -->  00:00:09,870
First, let's look at categorical ordinal data.

4

00:00:09,870  -->  00:00:11,955
Remember those dogs at the coffee shop?

5

00:00:11,955  -->  00:00:15,550
Let's say I give each a rating of how nice it is to me.

6

00:00:15,550  -->  00:00:19,590
Sometimes I shake hands with the dog and we become best friends.

7

00:00:19,590  -->  00:00:22,075
Other times, it pees on my shoe.

8

00:00:22,075  -->  00:00:25,935
I rate these interactions from very positive to very negative.

9

00:00:25,935  -->  00:00:31,000
These ranked categories are known as categorical ordinal data.

10

00:00:31,000  -->  00:00:33,255
Notice, this is different than the breeds,

11

00:00:33,255  -->  00:00:36,120
which are known as categorical nominal data,

12

00:00:36,120  -->  00:00:39,120
and do not have a rank order.
